articles.description: Miami coach Jim Larranaga felt ill prior to tipoff of Saturday's game against Boston College and remained in the locker room.
articles.headline: Miami coach Jim Larranaga misses game with illness

articles.description: Cameron Morse scored a season-high 28 points and Youngstown State held on to defeat IUPUI 84-80 on Saturday.
articles.headline: Morse has 28, leads Youngstown St past IUPUI 84-80

articles.description: Quinton Rose scored 16 of his 20 points in the second half when Temple pulled away from USF for its fifth-straight win 73-55 on Saturday.
articles.headline: Rose scores 20, Temple pulls away from USF 73-55

articles.description: Davion Mintz rises up inside the top of the key to sink a game-tying basket in the first half.

articles.description: Jalan McCloud had 20 points on 7-of-13 shooting and Devontavius Payne scored 11 points, including three 3-pointers, to help East Tennessee State beat VMI 70-56 on Saturday.
articles.headline: ETSU beats VMI, ties program record with 16th straight win
